{
  "stem": "10478.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A small group, they knew about it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the majority didn't know that, no.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well it was member of our church, and people I have contact with through an illegal magazine.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was a representative for that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I handed those people already beforehand 20 or 50 copies of that-- of that magazine, and got to know them, that they were-- I could trust them.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then through them I could find other places.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "First of all, like I say, I was using a different name, the name of Alexander.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I usually told people that they were not living in my state, or even in another city.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A couple times I had to transport a Jewish person-- persons from the railroad station to-- to my house for a couple of nights.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then when they walked from the railroad station to my house, instead of the north-- taking the normal normal route-- I took them and go all different route.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so that they could hardly could find a way back-- way back-- in case something would happen.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, of course.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had to have-- they had to have also an ID card, because you couldn't use their own ID card with a J on it.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we had to falsified stolen ID cards.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then a friend who was a student in high school, he pick-pocket coats from girls and men.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They usually had the ID card in their pocket.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because it was easier for the people to go to the police officer and say something stole my ID card, and you were honest about it.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that way we had somebody at the police office who was an artist.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he changed the picture and copied the stamp exactly like it was before.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
